# Project structure

- **Monorepo**: Use Turborepo for monorepo management
- **Package structure**: 
  - `apps/admin/` - Main admin application
  - `packages/ui/` - Shared UI components
  - `packages/database/` - Database schema and operations
  - `packages/form/` - Form components and utilities
  - `packages/tsconfig/` - Shared TypeScript configurations
- **App router**: Use Next.js App Router with route groups
- **File organisation**: Group related files in feature directories

## Directory structure

```
glint/
├── apps/
│   └── admin/
│       ├── src/
│       │   ├── app/           # Next.js App Router
│       │   ├── components/    # Shared components
│       │   ├── lib/          # Utilities and helpers
│       │   ├── schemas/      # Zod schemas
│       │   ├── trpc/         # TRPC routers and setup
│       │   └── types/        # TypeScript type definitions
│       └── tests/
│           └── e2e/          # End-to-end tests
├── packages/
│   ├── database/             # Database schema and operations
│   ├── form/                # Form components
│   ├── tsconfig/            # Shared TypeScript configs
│   └── ui/                  # UI components
```

## File organisation

- **Feature-based**: Group files by feature rather than type
- **Co-location**: Keep related files close together
- **Index files**: Use index files for clean exports
- **Route groups**: Use Next.js route groups for organisation
- **Shared code**: Extract shared code to packages

## Naming conventions

- **Files**: Use kebab-case for file names
- **Components**: Use PascalCase for component names
- **Functions**: Use camelCase for function names
- **Constants**: Use UPPER_SNAKE_CASE for constants
- **Types**: Use PascalCase for type and interface names
- **Directories**: Use kebab-case for directory names
- **Routes**: Use kebab-case for route segments
